---
import CardGrid from '../../components/CardGrid.astro';
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Player Guide"
  summary="The player-facing rules hub for character creation, archetypes, ka, combat, travel, and the strange rules of the road."
  eyebrow="Player reference"
  audience="player"
>
  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="content-lead">
      This guide is organized for table use rather than cover-to-cover reading. Start with
      character creation if you are building from scratch, or jump to pregens and Ka Points if you
      are joining a demo quickly.
    </p>
    <p>
      The book’s core player-facing loop is simple: build a wanderer, choose an archetype, learn
      what your Ka Points can do, and get comfortable with the rules for firearms, fear, travel,
      and strange powers. Everything else is there to help those scenes land.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Best Reading Order</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Read <strong>Character Creation</strong> to build your concept and sheet.</li>
        <li>Use <strong>Archetypes</strong> to choose the class fantasy that fits you.</li>
        <li>Learn <strong>Ka Points</strong> before your first session.</li>
        <li>Skim <strong>Combat</strong>, <strong>Firearms</strong>, and <strong>Travel</strong>.</li>
        <li>Check <strong>Downloads</strong> for quick references and pregens.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">What Matters Most At The Table</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The ka-tet is more important than solo heroics.</li>
        <li>Guns are deadly, loud, and often rare.</li>
        <li>The road itself is part of the game, not dead air between fights.</li>
        <li>Magic exists, but it should feel costly, strange, or mythic.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <CardGrid
      cards={[
        {
          title: 'Character Creation',
          summary: 'Follow the six-step path from concept to stats, gear, scars, and ka-tet bonds.',
          href: '/player-guide/character-creation',
          audience: 'player',
        },
        {
          title: 'Archetypes',
          summary: 'Compare all ten classes by fantasy, complexity, combat role, and story pressure.',
          href: '/player-guide/archetypes',
          audience: 'player',
        },
        {
          title: 'Core Rules',
          summary: 'Read the most-used mechanics, including firearms, fear, powers, and travel.',
          href: '/player-guide/rules',
          audience: 'player',
        },
        {
          title: 'Ka Points',
          summary: 'Learn the signature fate engine, how luck refreshes, and when the tet can share it.',
          href: '/player-guide/rules/ka-points',
          audience: 'player',
        },
        {
          title: 'Lore',
          summary: 'Learn the Tower, the Beams, Mid-World, gunslingers, thinnies, and the White.',
          href: '/lore',
          audience: 'player',
        },
        {
          title: 'Downloads',
          summary: 'Grab the quickstart, pregens, and cheat sheets for live play.',
          href: '/downloads',
          audience: 'player',
        },
      ]}
    />
  </section>
</ContentLayout>
